HEADWORD: body shop
<hw>body shop</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an establishment where the frame
or outer body of a vehicle may be repaired or painted; -- contrasted
with a <contr>mechanic</contr>, who repairs the motor and other working
components.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

